Task Manager - AI Campus Assignment
This is a full-featured, serverless web application for managing personal tasks, built as a submission for the AI Campus Assignment. The application is built from scratch using foundational web technologies and leverages Firebase for backend services.

Live Demo Link: https://task-manager-7c8a.onrender.com

Features
This application implements all the core and bonus features required by the assignment:

🔐 Authentication: Secure user sign-up and login functionality using email and password.

📝 Full CRUD Operations: Users can Create, Read, Update, and Delete their own personal tasks.

📊 Data Management:

Pagination: The task list is paginated to show a limited number of items per page.

Filtering: Tasks can be filtered by their priority level (Low, Medium, High).

Sorting: Tasks can be sorted by creation date, due date, or priority.

Search: A real-time, case-insensitive search to filter tasks by title.

** calculated Field:** Each task displays a dynamic timeUntilDue status (e.g., "Overdue," "Due today," "Due in 5 days") which is calculated from the dueDate and completed status.

✨ Modern UI:

A clean and responsive interface built with Tailwind CSS.

Dark Mode with a toggle to switch themes.

Loading indicators and custom modals for a smooth user experience.

Technology Stack
Frontend: HTML, Tailwind CSS, Vanilla JavaScript (ES6 Modules)

Backend & Database: Google Firebase (Authentication & Cloud Firestore)

Deployment: Render (Static Site Hosting)
